TESTING REPORT
Project: MindfulWork App — Smart Stress Relief Pod System
Testing Method: Usability Testing with Prototype
Number of Test Users: 5
Testing Tool Used: Figma / Canva Prototype Walkthrough

TEST USERS
User 1 — Female, 24, Intern
User 2 — Male, 35, Marketing Manager
User 3 — Female, 29, Customer Support Agent
User 4 — Male, 40, HR Executive
User 5 — Female, 31, Graphic Designer

TESTING PROCESS
Each user was asked to:

Log into the app
Check their stress level on the home screen
Book a pod session
Start a session and adjust pod settings
Complete a breathing exercise
Fill in the post-session journal
View their profile and preferences


OBSERVATIONS
User 1 — Sara, 24 | Intern

Navigated the home screen easily
Found the "How are you feeling right now?" check-in intuitive
Slightly confused about the difference between Book Pod and Start Session
Enjoyed the Breathe With Me screen and found the timer helpful
Suggestion: Add a short tooltip explaining what each button does

User 2 — Aryan, 35 | Marketing Manager

Immediately noticed the AI Suggestion banner and found it useful
Liked the MoodSync AI active banner on the Pod Control screen
Wanted more music options beyond Ambient
Found the journal sliders easy to use
Suggestion: Add more music genre options in preferences

User 3 — Saanvi, 29 | Customer Support Agent

Took a moment to find the Sessions tab
Liked the Upcoming / Past / Cancelled tabs layout
Found the stress reduction percentage on the journal very motivating
Suggestion: Make the Sessions tab more prominent in the bottom navigation

User 4 — Sameer, 40 | HR Executive

Found the app clean and easy to navigate
Appreciated the private and discreet design
Wanted a way to set the app to silent/do not disturb mode during sessions
Suggestion: Add a Do Not Disturb toggle on the Pod Control screen

User 5 — Emma, 31 | Graphic Designer

Loved the calming color scheme
Found the 7-day progress chart very clear and useful
Wanted the lighting slider on the Pod Control screen to show a preview of the color
Suggestion: Add a visual lighting preview when adjusting the slider


FEEDBACK SUMMARY
Home Screen clarity-4.6
AI Suggestion usefulness-4.8
Pod booking flow-4.2
Pod Control sliders-4.4
Breathe With Me screen-4.7
Post-Session Journal-4.5
Overall app experience-4.6

ITERATIONS MADE BASED ON FEEDBACK

Added tooltips on the home screen to clarify the difference between Book Pod and Start Session
Added more music genre options in the Profile preferences section
Made the Sessions tab slightly more prominent in the bottom navigation bar
Added a Do Not Disturb toggle consideration for future iterations of the Pod Control screen
Noted the lighting preview suggestion as a future enhancement for the Pod Control screen


CONCLUSION
Overall the prototype was received very positively by all 5 test users. 
The AI-driven personalization through MoodSync AI was highlighted as the standout feature. Users found the app intuitive, calming, and well-designed. 
The main areas for improvement involve adding more customization options and minor navigation clarity improvements. 
All critical features — stress tracking, pod scheduling, guided breathing, post-session journaling, and AI recommendations — were successfully understood and used by all test users without difficulty.
